    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Montreal</placeName>
                <date>10 Jany 5690</date>
            </p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir.</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)"><persName>Mr M Joseph</persName> has paid<lb/> me three dollars for
                a years subscription<lb/> to the Occident which I have requested<lb/>
                <persName>Miss Sarah J.</persName> to pay you, if on funds.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)"><persName>Mrs S. Benjamin</persName> has<lb/> written to inquire
                about the price<lb/> of a Bible bound in the manner<lb/> and for the purpose
                    <persName>Sarah J.</persName> will explain<lb/>—or has explained—to you. I
                only<lb/> refer to it to request you to intimate<lb/> to <persName>Mr S.
                    B.</persName> that he would oblige<lb/> by paying to me the amount he<lb/> owes
                you—this <add>בינינו</add>.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I enclose a review—not<lb/>
                <hi rend="underline">laudatory</hi> or <hi rend="underline">elaborate</hi> enough
                of<lb/> one of the best books I have ever</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>seen on the subject of the <add>?</add><lb/> I have paid some little attention
                to<lb/> this subject, but am better pleased<lb/> with <persName>Dr. D's</persName>
                book than with many<lb/> more pretentious ones. Any one<lb/> who has carefully read
                    <persName>Hugh<lb/> Millers</persName> Lestim<add>?</add> any of the Books<lb/>
                can well understand why he<lb/> shot himself. If I had been<lb/> an agent for an
                Insurance Office<lb/> where he had published and I<lb/> had read, I would not, if
                he<lb/> had applied to me have taken the risk.<lb/> And he has been
                immo<add>?</add><lb/> I think made too much of it.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)"><persName>Dr. D.</persName> has a claim on<lb/> Jews for a little
                    <add>שבח</add>. We<lb/> respect Hebrew learning and</p>
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p>the Hebrew language. True it is<lb/> that the Hebrew chair at McGill<lb/> College was
                filled by <add>?</add> years before<lb/>
                <persName>Dr. D.</persName> came to this country, and<lb/> I have not to thank him
                either for my<lb/> appointment, or for favoring the<lb/> chair. Yet I do thank him
                that he<lb/> has invariably in his published<lb/> writings shown how important
                is<lb/> the study of Hebrew to all. But <persName>Dr<lb/> D.</persName> has this
                special claim on us<lb/> just now. He is a learned naturalist<lb/>—a man of depth,
                and he is out<lb/> on <hi rend="underline">our</hi> side, and not on the<lb/> side
                of flippant shallow German<lb/> rationalists—who have imprudence<lb/> enough to
                spare.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I would recommend<lb/>
                <persName><sic>Dr. D.s</sic></persName> book to brother
                <persName>Wise</persName>—he<lb/> seems to be in agony just now on</p>
            <pb n="4"/>
            <p>the subject, and will no doubt<lb/> soon come out with a pragmatical<lb/>
                Introductory on the cosma<add>?</add><lb/> taking off his hat to
                    <persName>Adam</persName><lb/> &amp; <persName>Eve</persName>, for
                    re<add>?</add> with <persName>Abraham</persName><lb/> &amp; not them—but he will
                have<lb/> to turn the earth inside out to<lb/> get at the truth. The articles<lb/>
                in the Israelite on the historys<add>?</add> of<lb/> geology are printed as far as
                I<lb/> have noticed without a <add>?</add><lb/>
                <add>והרשות נתן וגו'</add></p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">If you print my notice<lb/> of <persName>Dr D's</persName> book,
                please do so at once<lb/> and address an additional copy<lb/> to <persName>Dr
                    D</persName>—to my care—</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">Remain Yrs truly</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">
                <persName role="author">Abraham de Sola</persName>
            </p>
            <p>Why do I never<lb/> hear from you<lb/> Will you oblige me by mailing the
                enclosed<lb/> for <persName>Andrew Cohen</persName>. I do not know his right
                address</p>
        </body>
    </text>
